description:
The [Symfony binary](https://symfony.com/download) is a must-have tool when developing Symfony applications on your local machine. It provides:

      * The best way to [create new Symfony applications](https://symfony.com/doc/current/setup.html#creating-symfony-applications);
      * A powerful [local web server](https://symfony.com/doc/current/setup/symfony_server.html) to develop your projects with support for [TLS certificates](https://symfony.com/doc/current/setup/symfony_server.html#enabling-tls);
      * A tool to [check for security vulnerabilities](https://symfony.com/doc/current/setup.html#security-checker);
      * Seamless integration with [Platform.sh](https://symfony.com/cloud).

       ## Technical Requirements

       * Install PHP 8.0.2 or higher and these PHP extensions (which are installed and enabled by default in most PHP 8 installations): Ctype, iconv, PCRE, Session, SimpleXML, and Tokenizer;
       * Install Composer, which is used to install PHP packages.

       This package **does not** depend on the [PHP](https://community.chocolatey.org/packages/php) or [Composer Setup](https://community.chocolatey.org/packages/composer) package.
